				<div class="message">A man sees a woman from across a room, and instantly notices how attractive she is to him. Due to this fact, he decides to go strike up a conversation with her; his first comment is specifically, &quot;Hey there, you are looking exceptionally pretty tonight.&quot; (Or something similar. A direct comment on her attractiveness).<br />
<br />
A) Was he being objectifying in this context and was it right or wrong, and B) if he wasn't, what would have pushed him over the line/where is the line.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I'm not Kaisann, but doesn't the answer to that depend on the room and what it's being used for?  If it's a workplace, that would be inappropriate and objectifying, but in a dating mixer it would be completely appropriate as an ice breaker.
